'''Google, Inc.''' ({{nasdaq|GOOG}} and {{lse|GGEA}}) is a [[search engine]] and a [[United States]] [[public company]], first [[Incorporation (business)|incorporated]] as a [[privately held company]] on [[7 September]] [[1998]]. The company had 9,378 full-time employees as of [[September 30]], 2006 and is based in [[Mountain View, California]]. [[Eric E. Schmidt|Eric Schmidt]], former [[chief executive officer]] of [[Novell]], was named Google's [[CEO]] when co-founder [[Lawrence E. Page|Larry Page]] stepped down.
